Title:

Inventory and Sales Management System using Assembly Language (MASM)

INTRODUCTION
The Inventory and Sales Management System is a console-based application developed using x86 Assembly Language with the MASM 6.15 assembler and Irvine32 library. The system is designed to simulate basic operations of a retail store, including inventory handling and sales processing.

This project demonstrates how low-level programming can be used to implement real-world applications by directly managing memory, registers, and control flow.

Objectives

- To understand low-level programming concepts using Assembly Language
- To implement a real-world system using MASM
- To practice memory management using arrays and data structures
- To develop modular programming using procedures
- To handle user input/output using Irvine32 library

